description: This file defines external API function prototypes for the Tod Client Object in the ANSC (Advanced Networking Service Container) framework. It includes license and copyright information, and declares functions for creating, removing, enrolling, and initializing the Tod Client object.

methods.name: AnscCreateTodClient
methods.description: Creates a new Tod Client object with provided container, owner, and reserved handles.

methods.name: AnscTodcoCreate
methods.description: Creates a new Tod Client Object instance.

methods.name: AnscTodcoRemove
methods.description: Removes the Tod Client Object instance.

methods.name: AnscTodcoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects for the Tod Client Object.
